Delta Lake
==========
Open source atorage framework that brings reliability to data lakes.
Delta lake is /isnot
-Open source technology // not proprietary technology.
-Storage framework/layer // storage format/medium
-Enabling building lakehouse // Data warehouse/Database service
Transaction Log - Known as Delta log, is ordered records of every transaction.
Single source of truth.
JSON file contains commit information
	-Operation performed + Predicated used
	-data files affected (added/removed)
Ex - we have writer process and reader process
Once the writer process starts, it stores the Delta Lake table in two data files in a parquet format.
As soon as the write process finishes writing, it adds the transaction log 000.json into the _delta_log directory.
A reader process always starts by reading a transaction log.
IN SECOND run, the writer process wants to update a record presents in the file number , But in Delta lake instead of updating the record in the file itself, it will make a copy of this file and make the necessary updates in that new file (file 3) It then updates the log by writing a new JOSN file. This new log file knows that file number 1 is no longer needed.
Hence it guarantees that you will get the most recent version of the data. Your read operation will never have a deadlock state or conflicts with any ongoing operation on the table.

