Change Data Capture
===================
Process of identifying changes made to data in the source and delivering those changes to the target.
Row level changes - Inserting new records, Updating existing records, Deleting existing records.
Row data + metadata

DLT supports CDC using CDC -  Apply changes into command
==========================
APPLY CHANGES INTO LIVE.target_table
FROM STREAM(LIVE.cdc_feed_table)
KEYS(key_filed)
APPLY AS DELETE WHEN operation_filed = "DELETE"
SEQUENCE BY sequence_filed
COLUMNS *

APPLY CHANGES INTO: Pros
=========================
1.Orders late-arriving records using the sequence key. This ensures that if any records arrive out of order, down stream result can be properly re-computed to reflect the updates.
2. It also enures that when records are deleted from a source table, these values are no longer reflected.
3.Default assumption is that rows will contain inserts and updates.
4.Can optionally apply deletes (APPLY as delete when condition)
5.Specify one or many fields as the primary key for a table.
6.Specify columns to ignore with the EXCEPT keyword.
7.Supportapplying changes as SCD type 1(default) or SCD type 2

Cons - Since data is being updated and deleted in the target table.
Breaks the append-only requirements for streaming table sources - can not perform streaming queries against the table. that means we will no longer be able to use this updated table as streaming sources later in the next layer.

